1
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,120
So you mean,

2
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:40,080
I can't have a different opinion.

3
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:43,240
No, you won't. I know you.

4
00:01:43,479 --> 00:01:45,920
You are open-minded and sensible.

5
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,160
You won't have a different opinion.

6
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,000
Yes.

7
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,120
You know me well.

8
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,960
Mr. Tian, the mooncakes are ready.

9
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:09,360
Setsuko, come eat some mooncakes.

10
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:10,520
Okay.

11
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:20,810
Did you have fun?

12
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:21,930
I had a lot of fun.

13
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,579
These are the Japanese mooncakes I made,

14
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:29,560
called Tsukimi Dango.

15
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,280
They are made of glutinous rice.

16
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:38,600
The yellow ones are covered with soybean flour,

17
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,800
and the red ones with red bean paste.

18
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:43,360
Ms. Ding,

19
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,329
have a taste.

20
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,840
Wanfu.

21
00:02:51,079 --> 00:02:53,210
What's the filling of your mooncakes?

22
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:59,520
Chef Jiao made Suzhou-style mooncakes.

23
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,450
They have ham, mixed nuts, and red bean paste.

24
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,400
I made Cantonese-style mooncakes.

25
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:09,080
There's a rose filling representing blooming flowers and a full moon,

26
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,140
and also egg yolk with red bean paste.

27
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:14,840
Please.

28
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,760
Ms. Ding

29
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,610
is allergic to glutinous rice.

30
00:03:29,079 --> 00:03:31,400
I think she should still prefer

31
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,680
the rose filling of Chinese mooncakes.

32
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:37,360
It's a holiday today, we should eat Chinese mooncakes.

33
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,440
Come.

34
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,440
Okay.

35
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:42,760
Please.

36
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:44,760
Thank you.

37
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,000
Come.

38
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,500
Thank you, Master.

39
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,200
Please sit.

40
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:15,600
You know we also celebrate the Mid-Autumn Festival in Japan.

41
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,480
Come, try the Japanese mooncakes too.

42
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,880
But you have to eat first.

43
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,400
If I don't eat first, won't you eat either?

44
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,000
Right.

45
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,240
If you don't eat first, I won't eat.

46
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,720
Then how about we eat together?

47
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,680
No, you eat first.

48
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:47,480
What's the difference between eating first or later?

49
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,480
Does it mean anything?

50
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,480
It means nothing.

51
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,770
I just want you to eat first.

52
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:56,400
Tian,

53
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,280
you still have the temper of a child.

54
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,840
Okay, then we'll eat first.

55
00:05:50,159 --> 00:05:51,200
Yueming,

56
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:54,220
Grandpa is going to find your mom for you.

57
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:59,409
We'll celebrate the Mid-Autumn Festival and eat mooncakes together.

58
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,120
Wanfu.

59
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,560
Wanfu.

60
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:48,040
Who by the river first saw the moon?

61
00:06:48,960 --> 00:06:54,440
When did the river moon first shine on men?

62
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:58,920
Generations of men come and go without end,

63
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:03,120
But the river moon remains the same year after year.

64
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:06,440
I know not who the river moon is waiting for,

65
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:11,400
I only see the Yangtze River sending the water away.

66
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,840
Yunkui.

67
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:35,760
You can't eat mooncakes over there, right?

68
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:41,840
Let us, Yujiao, and Yueming,

69
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:44,480
have a mooncake together

70
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,200
as a reunited family.

71
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:11,360
How about I ask my wife

72
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,680
to sing a song for us to liven things up?

73
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,600
Setsuko,

74
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,160
sing us a song.

75
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,880
Okay.

76
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:35,280
I am a sixteen-year-old girl from Manchuria.

77
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:39,440
In March, after the snow melts,

78
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:43,360
when the winter jasmine

79
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:47,760
is in full bloom,

80
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:52,400
I will marry into the neighboring village.

81
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:56,960
Brother Wang, please wait a little longer.

82
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:02,880
Send me off to marry with gongs and drums.

83
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,760
We Japanese like

84
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,850
to eat dumplings while admiring the moon.

85
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:11,760
The luckiest number is eating fifteen.

86
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,720
It symbolizes wholeness.

87
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:17,680
In some places, corresponding to the twelve months,

88
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,280
they eat twelve.

89
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,200
Have a little more.

90
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,760
I don't have that big of an appetite.

91
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,380
I'm afraid I'll burst.

92
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:30,320
Oh snow, ice, and cool wind,

93
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:34,440
blow to the edge of the northern sky.

94
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:40,080
Mother has made my beautiful wedding dress.

95
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:43,960
Mr. Tian, may I be excused?

96
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:46,240
You may.

97
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,480
Mr. Tian, I'll go take a look.

98
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:15,240
Mr. Tian.

99
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,640
Th-this is the servant's courtyard...

100
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,240
A servant.

101
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:25,080
Such a precious item,

102
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,120
he could never afford to compensate in his life.

103
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,850
He doesn't need to compensate.

104
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,320
He is my father.

105
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:32,400
Your father.

106
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,920
Didn't your father pass away?

107
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,300
His soul has returned.

108
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,000
He probably heard something he didn't like

109
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,330
and saw something he shouldn't have seen.

110
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:45,360
Father.

111
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,160
Father.

112
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,530
Yueming isn't here either.

113
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:53,760
Madam, wait a moment.

114
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,050
Flashlight.

115
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:01,720
Father.

116
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,000
Yueming.

117
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,080
Father.

118
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:11,960
Tian.

119
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,120
Don't call me Tian.

120
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,880
Don't call me Tian.

121
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:23,800
Bring material from home, but forage on the enemy.

122
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:26,040
Thus the army will have food enough.

123
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,760
You haven't stayed in China all these years for nothing.

124
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:31,280
You've studied 'The Art of War' thoroughly

125
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,000
and used it on me.

126
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,440
Using our factories and our resources

127
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:39,600
to sustain your war of destruction against us,

128
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,980
and sugarcoating it as cooperation.

129
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,640
Aren't you ashamed?

130
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,880
Kudo Shoichi.

131
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,080
I don't want my soap factory anymore.

132
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,460
I don't want it.

133
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,200
I don't care about your national policy,

134
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,560
or whatever.

135
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:56,320
Consider my money thrown down the drain.

136
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:57,760
Please leave.

137
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:02,440
Withdrawing at this time

138
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,320
means you are deliberately going against us.

139
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:08,320
You will be deemed a hostile element by the military.

140
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:12,360
All Tian's enterprises will be regarded as enemy property,

141
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:16,010
forcibly confiscated, and taken over by the Japanese Army.

142
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:20,040
Especially your machinery factory.

143
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,000
It has the most advanced machine tools in China

144
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:25,840
and the most skilled technicians.

145
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,260
With just a few minor modifications,

146
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,560
it can be converted at any time

147
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,970
into an arsenal for the Japanese Army.

148
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,040
Old classmate.

149
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,040
This is the last door

150
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,650
we've left open for you.

151
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,480
Don't shut it with your own hands.

152
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:45,960
Thank you.

153
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,160
Hurry up.

154
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,440
I'm afraid my father's ghost will come back

155
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,800
and smash your head.

156
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,400
Father.

157
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,600
Father.

158
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:53,880
Father.

159
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,400
Zhang Ruxian.

160
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,280
Zhang Ruxian.

161
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,520
Zhang Ruxian.

162
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,240
Father.

163
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,840
Hello.

164
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,200
Did you see an

165
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:16,570
old man with a white beard and a little boy?

166
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,000
The old man is about this tall,

167
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,160
and his beard is this long.

168
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:20,040
No.

169
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:21,800
Thank you.

170
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:25,360
Officer,

171
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,960
did you see an old man with a white beard

172
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,240
and a little boy?

173
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,240
No.

174
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:31,360
Thank you.

175
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,240
Master.

176
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,280
Wanfu.

177
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:20,480
It's so late.

178
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,960
Where did Master go? What should we do?

179
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,480
It's all my fault.

180
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:26,240
Why are you saying this now?

181
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:28,520
Master and Yueming couldn't have gone far.

182
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,280
You look over there, and I'll look here.

183
00:15:30,280 --> 00:15:31,560
Okay.

184
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,240
Wait.

185
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,320
Let's search together.

186
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,920
We shouldn't get separated.

187
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:37,680
This way.

188
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,080
Master.

189
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,600
Father.

190
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,000
Master.

191
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:54,360
Why would Master come to Juren Lane?

192
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,600
Isn't he asking for trouble?

193
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:56,400
Wanfu.

194
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:00,840
Don't cry.

195
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,960
Don't cry.

196
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:05,520
Grandpa is here.

197
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:06,960
Master.

198
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:10,400
Wanfu, look who's here.

199
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:11,880
Let's not cry.

200
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,760
Mommy will hold you.

201
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:14,640
Mommy is here.

202
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:15,810
Mommy will hold you.

203
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:17,520
Master.

204
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,240
Alright.

205
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,480
Why did you come here?

206
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,080
Yueming, don't cry.

207
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,720
Where else can I go?

208
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,360
I can only be here.

209
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,960
Let's go home.

210
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:27,200
I don't have a home.

211
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,320
No. 8 Juren Lane.

212
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,760
Master.

213
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,840
No. 8 Juren Lane is no longer our home.

214
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,560
Let's go back to where we live.

215
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:37,080
I don't have a home.

216
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,160
I can't go to that place anymore.

217
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,520
Master, what are you doing?

218
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:43,240
Father.

219
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:44,360
Yujiao.

220
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,080
Come back with me, Father.

221
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:45,960
Get up.

222
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,120
It's all my fault.

223
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:49,200
Being stubborn is useless.

224
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,360
You can take the child back.

225
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,040
Anyway, as for that place,

226
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,760
I can never go back.

227
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,600
Please go back, Father.

228
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,640
Get up.

229
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,360
Child, get up.

230
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,040
I won't get up until you come back.

231
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:01,520
You'll bring Fujita out.

232
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,320
Master.

233
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,520
You are driving me crazy.

234
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,680
Come back with me, Father, I beg you.

235
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,119
Master. Master.

236
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,160
Master.

237
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,440
Father. Father.

238
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,119
Let's go to the hospital.

239
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:31,280
Qi.

240
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,160
Qi. Qi.

241
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:36,960
Mr. Tian was right.

242
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,220
You guys are indeed in Juren Lane. Get in.

243
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,080
Mr. Tian.

244
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,160
The doctor has checked him

245
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,080
and said it's nothing serious.

246
00:18:43,520 --> 00:18:44,760
Thank you, Mr. Tian

247
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,760
for helping to call a doctor.

248
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,040
My father used to...

249
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:06,200
Yujiao.

250
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,800
You blame me

251
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,760
for my bad temper.

252
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:16,000
Having suffered such a big loss,

253
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,600
my temper is still that bad.

254
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:21,440
Yujiao, why did you and Wanfu

255
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:24,880
sing and dance with them?

256
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:28,040
I'm not foolish.

257
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,640
I want to endure,

258
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:35,000
but I just can't.

259
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:40,200
I've reached my limit. I'm not putting up with this anymore.

260
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,160
I've reached my limit.

261
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:45,640
The soldiers at the front line,

262
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:49,160
with grenades tied to their chests and backs,

263
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:53,120
crawled under the Japanese tanks.

264
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,960
I've reached my limit.

265
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:58,440
Patriotic merchants blew up their own cargo ships

266
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,440
and sank them to the bottom of the Yangtze River

267
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,240
to block the Japanese warships.

268
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:06,480
I've reached my limit.

269
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:10,320
The Chinese people make mountains collapse

270
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,760
and the sky change color.

271
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:16,560
Yunkui, am I right?

272
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,640
Mr. Tian.

273
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,680
Tomorrow,

274
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,570
I'd better take my father away.

275
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:32,920
Mr. Tian.

276
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,120
You don't have to pay us.

277
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:42,480
You mean this month's pay?

278
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:48,600
You don't have to pay my wife either.

279
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,120
Do you know

280
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:55,400
how much the pair of vases you broke

281
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:56,840
is worth?

282
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,160
A pair?

283
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:02,080
No, didn't my father just break one?

284
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,400
A pair.

285
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:07,000
Even if you combine your wages,

286
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:12,260
you can't afford to pay for them if you work in the Tian Mansion for the rest of your lives.

287
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,850
Still want to leave?

288
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,040
No one is going anywhere.

289
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,560
Have a mooncake.

290
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:49,920
Have a mooncake. Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

291
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:26,120
Mr. Tian.

292
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,640
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

293
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:34,880
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

294
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,280
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival,

295
00:23:05,320 --> 00:23:06,640
have a mooncake.

296
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,480
Thank you.

297
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:10,720
Thank you.

298
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,930
Are today's mooncakes delicious?

299
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:37,760
Yes.

300
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:42,160
I made all the red bean paste ones,

301
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,020
that's the only one I learned from Wanfu.

302
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,120
Marrying a good cook

303
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,880
must be very happy.

304
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,800
Of course.

305
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:59,120
Especially Baozi and egg drop soup,

306
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:01,040
Wanfu's Baozi

307
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,370
is the most delicious in the world.

308
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,680
On the Shanghai Battlefield...

309
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:10,360
I also met a good cook.

310
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:13,240
He could use water caltrops to make mooncake filling.

311
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:15,840
He used a shell casing to shape the mooncakes perfectly round.

312
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,900
And they tasted exceptionally good.

313
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:24,740
Can your wife make mooncakes?

314
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:27,840
No, she can't.

315
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:30,240
She is a young lady from a wealthy family.

316
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:32,160
She has never done any household chores.

317
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:34,290
She doesn't know how to cook anything.

318
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,080
But she can boil broad beans.

319
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:39,960
The broad beans she boils are especially delicious.

320
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,760
To me,

321
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:45,610
they are the most delicious food in the world.

322
00:24:55,520 --> 00:25:02,760
♪ The crescent moon shines over many lands ♪

323
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:10,160
♪ Some families are happy, some are sad ♪

324
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:17,760
♪ Some couples share the same bed ♪

325
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:25,320
♪ The others
are scattered across the land ♪

326
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:49,800
Find someone to set a fire.

327
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,210
Burn down Pudong Soap Factory.

328
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:54,600
Set a fire.

329
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,890
Burn down Pudong Soap Factory.

330
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:58,880
Yes, sir.

331
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,400
Move to the sides.

332
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:07,810
Don't block the middle.

333
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:09,960
Dr. Luo! Dr. Luo!

334
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:11,440
This wounded soldier is in a deep coma.

335
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,320
He needs emergency treatment.

336
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:12,760
Is he conscious?

337
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:13,000
Hurry.

338
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:13,800
Hurry, hurry.

339
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,400
Come on, take him to the operating room immediately. Hurry!

340
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,440
Okay.

341
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:45,930
Weak breathing.

342
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:48,560
Report. The road is blocked by Japanese firepower.

343
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:49,880
The backup vehicles can't get through.

344
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,760
Currently, the Japanese army is only a few li away from the hospital.

345
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:52,960
They are advancing rapidly into our territory.

346
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:56,160
Orders from above: the hospital is to evacuate on its own.

347
00:26:56,840 --> 00:26:57,320
Go.

348
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,360
Dr. Luo! Dr. Luo!

349
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,280
Dr. Luo!

350
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:03,880
This soldier needs surgery immediately.

351
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:04,480
Hurry.

352
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:08,360
Director, the main forces have retreated.

353
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:09,400
Let's run too.

354
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:09,880
Yeah.

355
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,000
If we all run away,

356
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:12,540
what about these wounded?

357
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:14,520
The army doesn't care about us anymore.

358
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:16,040
How can we care about the wounded?

359
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:17,360
We can't just leave them.

360
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:19,160
Okay. Everyone, listen to me.

361
00:27:19,360 --> 00:27:20,600
We are doctors.

362
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,040
Our duty is to heal the wounded and rescue the dying.

363
00:27:23,040 --> 00:27:25,360
We must consider the sick and wounded.

364
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,120
We must make a decision now.

365
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:30,200
Either break out or surrender.

366
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,280
Breaking out is a suicide mission.

367
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,120
Let's surrender.

368
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:32,640
Yeah. Exactly.

369
00:27:32,640 --> 00:27:34,760
Surrender? I'd rather die.

370
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,200
The war has come to this.

371
00:27:36,240 --> 00:27:38,160
Haven't we seen enough blood every day?

372
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,920
Let's risk our lives and fight the Japanese!

373
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,040
It's easy for you to say.

374
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,000
How many people are here now?

375
00:27:44,360 --> 00:27:46,120
The sick and wounded are all in the room.

376
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:47,320
How many can fight?

377
00:27:47,440 --> 00:27:48,560
How many guns and bullets do we have?

378
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:49,680
Don't you know?

379
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:50,320
Exactly.

380
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:52,360
Director, I agree to surrender.

381
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:53,280
I also agree to surrender.

382
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:54,560
If we don't surrender, we'll just die in vain.

383
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,420
I survived Shanghai and Nanjing.

384
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,320
Wherever the Japanese army goes,

385
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:00,000
they stab everyone they see with bayonets.

386
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:02,280
If we surrender, can you guarantee they won't kill us?

387
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,040
Then we can't just go die for nothing.

388
00:28:04,040 --> 00:28:06,040
We're all wounded. How can we fight?

389
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,960
I support breaking out. We must.

390
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:08,600
Alright.

391
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:09,960
Stop arguing.

392
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:10,960
Stop.

393
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:11,800
Stop arguing.

394
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,920
Let's decide democratically, one person, one vote.

395
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,280
Let's vote by a show of hands.

396
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:19,200
Voting is fine. I choose to surrender.

397
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,800
Surrender. I surrender too.

398
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,720
Why do you want to surrender?

399
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,320
Stop arguing.

400
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:39,650
What about the wounded?

401
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,290
Let's not push our luck.

402
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:49,100
What the Japanese did in Nanjing,

403
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,440
do you think when they reach Wuhan

404
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:52,100
they won't dare to do it again?

405
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:53,600
There is no democracy on the battlefield.

406
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,360
Voting cannot decide right or wrong.

407
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:57,020
Now there is only one way to go:

408
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:57,840
break out.

409
00:28:58,120 --> 00:28:58,800
Who are you?

410
00:28:58,840 --> 00:28:59,880
What do you do?

411
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:00,520
Yeah.

412
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:01,880
Why should we listen to you?

413
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:02,840
Yeah, we've never seen you before.

414
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:04,120
Which regiment are you from? Yeah.

415
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,840
Director, what we are discussing now is...

416
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,360
He is a Brigade Commander, Major General.

417
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:08,490
Brigade Commander?

418
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,120
Our hospital is full of hidden talents.

419
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:12,200
A Brigade Commander, Major General pops up at this time.

420
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,160
He is my cousin,

421
00:29:13,280 --> 00:29:14,920
Brigade Commander Zhang Yunkui of the 87th Brigade.

422
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:17,120
Zhang Yunkui? Seems he was in the newspaper.

423
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,720
Zhang Yunkui of the 87th Brigade,

424
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:20,040
why is this so familiar?

425
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:22,400
I am from the 187th Division of the 130th Army,

426
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:24,880
former Brigade Commander of the 87th Brigade, Zhang Yunkui.

427
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,340
He is the runaway general.

428
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:28,280
How dare you!

429
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,400
You harmed a bunch of our buddies in the Battle of Shanghai,

430
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,840
now you're here to harm us again, right?

431
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:33,570
What nonsense are you talking?

432
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:36,560
Alright,

433
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:37,760
stop talking.

434
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,400
Brigade Commander Zhang,

435
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:42,000
I don't know about your past,

436
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:45,600
but among everyone present,

437
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:47,200
you have the highest rank.

438
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:50,200
Whatever arrangements you have, we'll listen to you.

439
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:52,280
Director.

440
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,330
Director, you can't listen to him.

441
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:56,840
Move out of the way!

442
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,000
The Japanese vanguard is almost here.

443
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,160
If they catch up,

444
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:05,580
it will be too late.

445
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,680
All in uniform, prepare to break out.

446
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:09,810
Non-combatants, prepare to retreat.

447
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,760
We are military doctors.

448
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:13,220
We don't know how to fight.

449
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,160
My wife is waiting for me.

450
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:17,880
Worst comes to worst, I won't wear this uniform.

451
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:18,600
I want to go home.

452
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:19,600
I don't want to die, Director.

453
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:20,600
Try taking off this uniform.

454
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:23,000
If you do, you're a deserter.

455
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:24,520
I'm a deserter?

456
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:27,120
You have the nerve to call me a deserter?

457
00:30:27,120 --> 00:30:29,160
You are the biggest deserter!

458
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:30,200
What are you trying to do?

459
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,080
What?

460
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,840
Squad Leader of Squad Three, let him go.

461
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:39,920
Listen clearly.

462
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:41,640
If I were a deserter,

463
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,960
I wouldn't be attending this meeting.

464
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,080
When we break out later,

465
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,540
everyone with a gun can keep a close eye on me.

466
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,600
If I show any sign of running away,

467
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:51,200
you can shoot me.

468
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:53,160
Including you.

469
00:30:57,480 --> 00:31:00,000
Brigade Commander Zhang, please continue.

470
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:02,120
Squad Leader of Squad Three, Zhou.

471
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:02,480
Here.

472
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:03,240
Here.

473
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:04,440
Go check the direction of the Japanese

474
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:05,520
and see how soon they will arrive.

475
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:06,000
Yes.

476
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:06,680
Yang Yuanzheng.

477
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:07,120
Here.

478
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:07,720
Go check the surrounding area

479
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,680
to see if there are other troops, and ask for reinforcements.

480
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:10,240
Yes.

481
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:10,940
Lao You.

482
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:11,400
Here.

483
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,360
Go see how many wounded soldiers can still hold a gun

484
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:15,480
to assist our guard squad in the breakout.

485
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:15,840
Yes.

486
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:17,400
All unarmed personnel

487
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:18,560
and the other nurses

488
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,720
should assist the severely wounded in retreating.

489
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:21,920
Remember, everyone,

490
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:23,800
no flashlights on the way,

491
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:25,010
and no making noise.

492
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:26,920
Light one lamp for every fifteen people.

493
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:29,050
Remember, do not expose our position.

494
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:31,600
Brigade Commander Zhang, we follow your command.

495
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,400
Everyone, break out towards the bridge.

496
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:35,360
No, we can't take the bridge.

497
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,080
It's easy for the Japanese to spot us.

498
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,400
Remember clearly, everyone.

499
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:40,440
Go along the back mountain, cross the mountain,

500
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:42,440
pass the waterfall, then head southwest.

501
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,480
Cross another mountain,

502
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,400
and you'll find an abandoned machinery factory.

503
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:46,320
It's getting dark now.

504
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:48,120
The Japanese are also afraid of being ambushed,

505
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:49,720
so their main force generally won't advance.

506
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,080
We'll strive to break out first,

507
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:53,520
and then move towards the river when the time is right.

508
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,440
Once we have boats,

509
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:55,370
we will survive.

510
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:56,480
Okay.

511
00:31:56,760 --> 00:31:58,080
Zuliang, Xiaoyue.

512
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,480
Quickly arrange for people

513
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:01,920
to sort and pack those materials and documents.

514
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,360
And don't lose that batch of Sanqi and Safflower.

515
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:05,840
Director, we won't bring the heavy Chinese medicine bags

516
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:06,960
or the equipment.

517
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:09,040
Everyone, remember, any documents we can't take

518
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,800
that involve designations and names

519
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:12,640
must be destroyed on the spot. Travel light.

520
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:13,160
Got it?

521
00:32:13,280 --> 00:32:14,000
Got it.

522
00:32:14,120 --> 00:32:15,480
Distribute weapons and execute.

523
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:16,160
Yes.

524
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,080
Go.

525
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,240
Hurry.

526
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,400
Hurry up.

527
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,680
Hurry, take good care of him.

528
00:32:38,680 --> 00:32:39,280
Yes.

529
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:42,840
Keep up.

530
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,400
Miss Xiaoyue, be careful too.

531
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:08,720
Come.

532
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:17,080
Keep quiet and speed up.

533
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:52,480
This way.

534
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:53,320
Okay.

535
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,050
Is everyone out?

536
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:56,840
Brigade Commander Zhang,

537
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,360
all personnel have evacuated.

538
00:33:58,360 --> 00:33:58,720
Go.

539
00:33:58,880 --> 00:33:59,400
Go.

540
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:01,440
Go.

541
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:09,880
Go.

542
00:34:20,719 --> 00:34:21,650
Brother Hechen.

543
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:24,560
Did you read the newspaper? Wuhan has fallen.

544
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,600
I didn't. I heard it on the radio.

545
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,080
The state of our nation is so bleak.

546
00:34:29,080 --> 00:34:30,600
At the front lines,

547
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:33,760
our soldiers have become piles of wandering ghosts.

548
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:36,080
I must write a powerful article

549
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:38,000
to mourn their heroic spirits

550
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:42,000
and commemorate this day of national grief.

551
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:44,960
Are you going to the front lines?

552
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:47,360
I have connections

553
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:49,800
that can get you directly to Hankou.

554
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:53,080
I didn't say I was going to Hankou.

555
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:55,480
What's the use of such sorrow?

556
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,120
Every time I talk to you about serious matters,

557
00:34:58,120 --> 00:35:00,180
you have this indifferent attitude.

558
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:01,560
Look at this newspaper.

559
00:35:01,560 --> 00:35:02,890
There's news about you.

560
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:06,760
The Imperial Japanese Army returns Chinese businesses in Shanghai.

561
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:09,960
Tian Jiatai Soap Factory to be jointly run by China and Japan.

562
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,280
Your news.

563
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:14,020
I heard it on the radio too.

564
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:15,530
You knew it already.

565
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:17,760
Your friend Kudo,

566
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,800
didn't he keep claiming

567
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:21,600
to be a pacifist?

568
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:23,600
Suddenly,

569
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,920
he joined a Japanese national policy company.

570
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:28,720
People of different races have different hearts.

571
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:32,960
The loyal are often butchers,

572
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:35,920
while the ungrateful are often scholars.

573
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:38,440
That despicable man.

574
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:42,680
The war has reached this stage.

575
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,280
There's no personal identity,

576
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:47,560
only national stance.

577
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:50,480
He's clearly forcing your hand.

578
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:52,040
He wants to confirm

579
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:54,960
that you are a traitor.

580
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,840
What should I do, Ruisheng?

581
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:00,120
Please help me write an article

582
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:01,760
to clear my name.

583
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:04,380
I won't hesitate to write an article for you.

584
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:06,000
But once you are confirmed

585
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,560
as a traitor,

586
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,000
even if I write ten articles,

587
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:11,440
it won't help.

588
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:20,960
Assassins sent from Chongqing

589
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,780
might already be on their way.

590
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:35,640
Mr. Shao is the Secretary-General of the city.

591
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:36,480
Now he is surrounded

592
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:38,880
by Japanese Gendarmerie wherever he goes,

593
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,930
and rides in a bulletproof car.

594
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,600
What about you?

595
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:46,920
What about me?

596
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:53,000
Can I buy a bulletproof car like Mr. Shao's?

597
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:55,760
That's not what we're talking about.

598
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,440
I've thought of three options for you.

599
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,840
You decide for yourself.

600
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:01,060
Mr. Shao approached me

601
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,180
to run a newspaper for him.

602
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,640
I managed to fob him off.

603
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:08,080
But his ultimate goal

604
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:10,200
was to get me to persuade you

605
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:11,920
to work for him.

606
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:22,240
I guessed you wouldn't agree.

607
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,700
So the first option is out.

608
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:25,200
The second option,

609
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,000
never take a puppet position.

610
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,400
We can use Lin Changgeng

611
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,320
to protect you.

612
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:31,960
Lin Changgeng?

613
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:34,440
The man Mr. Shao brought last time?

614
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:37,560
Yes, although he's backed by the Japanese,

615
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:38,880
he associates

616
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:41,400
with anyone who has money.

617
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,600
Now he's upgraded.

618
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,160
With guns and men,

619
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:48,410
your safety wouldn't be a problem.

620
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:50,520
If I use Lin Changgeng,

621
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:54,080
I'll be considered a traitor even if I'm not.

622
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:55,760
You want to stay out of it,

623
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:59,520
but all three sides want a piece of you.

624
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:01,600
What's the third option?

625
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:03,560
The third option is

626
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:05,960
to give up your factory in the Chinese sector

627
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,440
and leave Shanghai.

628
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:09,680
Hong Kong or Chongqing, either is fine.

629
00:38:09,680 --> 00:38:12,680
And without delay.

630
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:18,600
Thank you for thinking of three options for me, Ruisheng.

631
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:21,120
Let me think about it.

632
00:38:23,160 --> 00:38:25,080
Okay, I have to go now.

633
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:27,320
Don't go yet. Wait a moment.

634
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:28,480
The coffee will be ready soon.

635
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:31,800
I have things to do at the newspaper office. I'm leaving now.

636
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:32,660
These two days,

637
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:34,720
as soon as there's news about you in the newspaper,

638
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,200
I will bring it to you immediately.

639
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:37,720
Think carefully about your own affairs.

640
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,580
No need. I can hear it on the radio.

641
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:41,200
Whenever I talk to you about serious business,

642
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,840
you always have this attitude.

643
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,700
I won't say anymore. I'm leaving.

644
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,160
Mr. Jin.

645
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:56,080
Mr. Tian.

646
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:58,800
The brothers we sent over were all stopped.

647
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:01,640
There are patrolling Gendarmeries everywhere inside and outside the factory.

648
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:03,640
The Japanese are worried that Chongqing will cause sabotage,

649
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:04,920
so it's heavily guarded.

650
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:06,320
We can't burn it tonight.

651
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:09,320
I was thinking, we should still look for an opportunity

652
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:11,800
to let the master workers secretly sabotage the machines.

653
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,480
It would be best to make it look like an accident

654
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:14,640
and cause a fire.

655
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:17,640
Also, Mr. Tian.

656
00:39:17,920 --> 00:39:19,240
Things are too tense these days.

657
00:39:19,240 --> 00:39:20,440
You better not go out.

658
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:21,480
Don't go out.

659
00:39:24,120 --> 00:39:25,450
But these past few days,

660
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:28,760
several friends invited me out at the same time.

661
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:32,890
Whoever invited you out is from the Military Bureau of Investigation.

662
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:40,960
Liu Sheng.

663
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,040
Young Master Bei.

664
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,000
Didn't these people all follow Mr. Shao

665
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,800
and join the puppet government?

666
00:39:50,960 --> 00:39:54,840
They want to use my life as a pledge of loyalty,

667
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,980
to serve Chongqing and have a foot in both camps.

668
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:00,200
They want to use me to gain credit,

669
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:01,640
so that one day in the future,

670
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:03,240
they can reduce their own crimes.

671
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:05,720
These people are too despicable and vicious.

672
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:07,040
You absolutely cannot go.

673
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:08,920
If I don't go today or tomorrow,

674
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:11,760
I can't let the guns of the Military Bureau of Investigation

675
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:13,290
point at me forever, right?

676
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:15,730
I should at least have a chance to explain.

677
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:17,240
Am I supposed to

678
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:20,800
stay indoors for the rest of my life?

679
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:23,400
Sir, if you insist on going,

680
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:25,480
I will add two more layers of guards.

681
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:29,370
The coffee is ready.

682
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:06,680
Clear.

683
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:07,240
Zhou.

684
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:07,880
Okay.

685
00:41:10,080 --> 00:41:10,840
Clear.

686
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:11,920
It's clear. Come here quickly.

687
00:41:11,920 --> 00:41:14,400
Hurry. Hold on.

688
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:18,480
Slow down.

689
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:20,300
Be careful.

690
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,320
Go.

691
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:27,760
Take the high ground.

692
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:42,640
Zuliang, take care of the wounded.

693
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,480
Bandage them up.

694
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,600
Okay, understood.

695
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,540
What are you doing?

696
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:47,840
I'm checking his injuries.

697
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:48,840
Don't light torches or oil lamps

698
00:41:48,840 --> 00:41:50,300
so we won't be discovered.

699
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:51,640
Lao You, Yuanzheng,

700
00:41:51,720 --> 00:41:52,480
come with me to check the front.

701
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:53,000
Okay.

702
00:41:59,120 --> 00:41:59,720
Sit down.

703
00:42:00,880 --> 00:42:01,360
Come.

704
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,000
Sit here.

705
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:03,520
Tell the people behind us

706
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:05,000
not to light lamps or torches.
